Chapter: The Banking Module

 This module models a simple banking system. An account belongs to a
 person, holds a balance, and supports deposits and withdrawals.
 Balances are never negative.

Section: Data Model

 An Account is a record containing:
 - owner : Text
 - balance : Integer

 TransactionResult is either:
 - Success (newBalance : Integer)
 - InsufficientFunds (requested : Integer, available : Integer)

Section: Operations

 To deposit (amount : Integer) into (account : Account):

  deposit : Integer -> Account -> Account
  deposit (amount) (account) =
    Account { owner = account.owner, balance = account.balance + amount }

 To withdraw (amount : Integer) from (account : Account):

  withdraw : Integer -> Account -> TransactionResult
  withdraw (amount) (account) =
    if account.balance >= amount
      then Success { newBalance = account.balance - amount }
      else InsufficientFunds { requested = amount, available = account.balance }

Section: Entry Point

 We say:

  main : Text
  main = "Banking module loaded"
